from pyspark.sql.types import StructType, StructField, StringType, IntegerType, DoubleType, ArrayType
from pyspark.sql.functions import *
from pyspark.sql.window import Window
from faker import Faker
import datetime

# data lake and container information
storage_account = 'stoeadaihackathon'
use_test_env = False

if use_test_env:
    stage1np = 'abfss://test-env@' + storage_account + '.dfs.core.windows.net/stage1np'
    stage2np = 'abfss://test-env@' + storage_account + '.dfs.core.windows.net/stage2np'
    stage2p = 'abfss://test-env@' + storage_account + '.dfs.core.windows.net/stage2p'
else:
    stage1np = 'abfss://stage1np@' + storage_account + '.dfs.core.windows.net'
    stage2np = 'abfss://stage2np@' + storage_account + '.dfs.core.windows.net'
    stage2p = 'abfss://stage2p@' + storage_account + '.dfs.core.windows.net'

dfUsersRaw = spark.read.format('csv').load(f'{stage1np}/m365/AAD/users/users.csv', header='true')
dfPersonIdentifierRaw = spark.read.format('csv').load(f'{stage1np}/m365/DIPData/Roster/PersonIdentifier.csv', header='false')
dfPersonRaw = spark.read.format('csv').load(f'{stage1np}/m365/DIPData/Roster/Person.csv', header='false')

# Method for extracting the data in "PersonIdentifier.csv" and allocating to "userPrincipalName" and "id" (both located within _c1 above).
num_of_new_users_and_ids = dfPersonIdentifierRaw.count()
users_or_ids = dfPersonIdentifierRaw.select('_c1').collect()
list_of_pi1pi2 = dfPersonIdentifierRaw.select('_c0').collect()

num_of_new_users = dfPersonRaw.count()
list_of_stAndT = dfPersonRaw.select('_c0').collect()
usersFirstName = dfPersonRaw.select('_c1').collect()
usersLastName = dfPersonRaw.select('_c3').collect()

usersSchema = StructType(fields=[
    StructField('givenName', StringType(), False),
    StructField('surname', StringType(), False),
    StructField('userPrincipalName', StringType(), False),
    StructField('id', StringType(), False)
])

dfNewUsersGen = spark.createDataFrame([], usersSchema)

tPlaceHolder = 1
stPlaceHolder = 1
namePlaceHolder = 1

for n in range(num_of_new_users_and_ids):
    if list_of_pi1pi2[n][0] == "edp_pi1_st" + str(stPlaceHolder):
        uPN = users_or_ids[n][0]
        userId = users_or_ids[n+1][0]
        userGivenName = usersFirstName[namePlaceHolder-1][0]
        userSurname = usersLastName[namePlaceHolder-1][0]
        newRow = spark.createDataFrame([(userGivenName, userSurname, uPN, userId)])
        
        dfNewUsersGen = dfNewUsersGen.union(newRow)
        stPlaceHolder = stPlaceHolder + 1
        namePlaceHolder = namePlaceHolder + 1

    elif list_of_pi1pi2[n][0] == "edp_pi1_t" + str(tPlaceHolder):
        uPN = users_or_ids[n][0]
        userId = users_or_ids[n+1][0]
        userGivenName = usersFirstName[namePlaceHolder-1][0]
        userSurname = usersLastName[namePlaceHolder-1][0]
        newRow = spark.createDataFrame([(userGivenName, userSurname, uPN, userId)])

        dfNewUsersGen = dfNewUsersGen.union(newRow)
        tPlaceHolder = tPlaceHolder + 1
        namePlaceHolder = namePlaceHolder + 1

    else: 
        n = n+0

dfNewUsers = dfNewUsersGen
display(dfNewUsers)

num_of_new_users = dfNewUsers.count()
oldUserIds = dfUsersRaw.select('id').collect()
newUserIds = dfNewUsers.select('id').collect()
deviceStrippedIds = dfNewDevices.select('strippedIds').collect()

    StructField('oldId', StringType(), False),
    StructField('newId', StringType(), False)
])

dfDeviceIdRef = spark.createDataFrame([], deviceIdSchema)

for n in range(num_of_new_users):
    userOldId = oldUserIds[n][0]
    userNewId = newUserIds[n][0]
